<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/46667560-robert-irish"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1493082399i/46667560._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/46667560-robert-irish">Robert Irish</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    I think it's marvellous that Bruno was imaginary. Why else did he miss the train? Why else did Leo have to order the donuts? Why else was the flour fr<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    I think it's marvellous that Bruno was imaginary. Why else did he miss the train? Why else did Leo have to order the donuts? Why else was the flour from the attempt at a cake in his apartment rather than in Bruno's? It all kind of makes sense when you realize that Bruno was just a figment. I did not see it coming, but it adds a sudden richness to the crazy character of Leo Gursky. <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
